Demo of a possible interface for OOF3D, modeled after the graphics
window in OOF2.  This loads the 3D microstructure data which is in the
pgm or mini directories and stored as slices.  The widgets allow you
to control the view.

To run you will need to have:

1.  oof2 installed in a path known to python
2.  vtk with python vtk installed
3.  gtkglext and pygtkglext

To run, type "python demo3d.py"

